[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating native tests and resources**\n\nI’m considering that during a native test, the agent from the JVM can collect resource access and add resources. It seems like the test resources are generated under native-image. It’s interesting that the default conditional agent collects metadata from execution, which likely uses the agent. So, resource access in JVM adds class resources to the metadata. However, there's a rule against writing, and Forge handles that. I'm also noting that direct dynamic class loading might fail in native after reading a resource. Interesting!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00052007b4fb7ca0016a297232d84c8197959a83019de3011d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKXJFzI4QgGlc_HN8Nwi5FQSoeYebg6_tYd3-EEZUo812xHWgFvHsK7qQ_OuQHpdLFkzYjgQ9gd9RtNb26B1oKnREeKLFCTEoAyGJ1hKI9AflyKqw8owwz3BKRO09FUqecq0he0R7kmLa3a-MioZYP7BhMEc6-udh7IuH1CMGP8QjwnHOOBykLcmTdRsEmncjw3FF7mnWmYHvRuZgcqdo33LxU0rQtD7jRj1YwxkLzfiGYLwui7OBe47ufMbVBwm2zpTwbjVsWeNcbh4-DBYY9PfMaqbqyyiz5t1pbKOnTkmWFO6pQRj594oGDX5LNmJ1CEApx0uB6RU1GT8_fLIuT5tER_cJ7vVKCEi1WtpBW24OOqKHlJTf7mEnTHWmLmBayr7yPhlyhZjOgWtnkSEayHS4-QJW7eESzaG-4N2fMh2zSMMaqGyVr9iABmFloSTKRlNNarjG23OAmW5IB9TkVADMn0HdepmAaN2pMNiIwogBH9rr4aMrHnwGxLkYVqa2CmkEymSgegMDBFnzOeho_q-xydQNIr3FBnu-OG0NqdNnMSLcx4XNZ-Rua0Y3FgvU1Mt46_R3CSS9_fBPbic4U3CGCisNlp8yjnEVOu0jSEhSsfpiBgpzC1kJnZOo1ZDx-KoRZ1HlEjnwvnuydR7tOwpCXsDFbC_t-dJTk0ZDyTyEEBPyMLTK-JY7IC2pNdYeodUMXrXzRr2F2iNgh5LFZw1kj7VLq3oNF3tqhKdy9kBgFVJkMimBU-vQO0AshFVA-4NbZnVY2Lx2hfpx9cm2JDNb6gVMGPuoMp9zxJU2TL2cJ1BVkDupwGfhESDh-COjohOu1dgaPCqBD1iSrCGDNdSjJwBhKL7iIXo8JWM0eHS7Z3xT-F4be8SaWbvBIHK8lvBZm0e1xEazmcEOLDNTw7seGKXfyvbO5YpBJJtJ-o5rDsxP9aDaKpaYKOem8gvilSevp09HiLU0WCT9JzNC3SeMhgWM5WLP-VYH6QiSmu3KaSCXxK1j6yHbqtVPvrSjVMKuNnquAQaWuO-h3ZOZdDpElTyliFoed9iF4Eg4hMgyNJoJnrzUOJTK4-BPUe3IwtqG1WPUJ_P8dJwxnj6zxmqovtbwJKPnbJTtIYSWkDM0mrfvDcV2PBFZKXaUcG